news.title: FAA prohibits most private jets at 12 major airports amid shutdown's air traffic staffing problems
news.summary: The new restrictions come less than a week after the FAA ordered commercial airlines to cut flights due to air traffic controller staffing shortfalls. The new restrictions are expected to be in effect for the rest of the year.

news.title: SNAP benefits: Appeals court again rejects Trump admin bid to halt full payment order
news.summary: The question of whether the Trump administration can be compelled to pay 42 million Americans full food stamp benefits is set to return to the Supreme Court.

news.title: As private tech market heats up, PitchBook makes startup data available via ChatGPT
news.summary: PitchBook is launching PitchBook Navigator, a new generative AI tool that produces private market insights. The tool produces insights based on user prompts.

news.title: Instacart tops third-quarter expectations under new CEO Rogers, gives strong guidance
news.summary: Instacart said it's expanding artificial intelligence tools, and recently launched a suite of new solutions for grocers. Instacart: "We are constantly looking for ways to improve our customer experience"

news.title: Trump's 'No tax on tips' could be end of large-group service fees on restaurant bills
news.summary: President Trump's 'no tax on tips' may end it, but restaurants aren't happy. If you don't like service fees restaurants charge large groups, you may be in luck.

news.title: Here’s how high tariff rates would have to rise to bring manufacturing back to its glory days. Even Trump would be shocked.
news.summary: Economists at UBS point to analysis done by the center-right American Enterprise Institute. They say tariffs would have to be set at 42.5% to level out manufacturing imports and exports.

news.title: Who is reshaping the way we live, work, spend and invest? Meet the MarketWatch 25.
news.summary: The leaders and thinkers whose ideas have impacted the way the government, companies and American society at large are grappling with technological change, higher prices and more.

news.title: Pfizer won its fight to buy an obesity-drug maker. It took an extra $1.7 billion and a phone call.
news.summary: Pfizer is buying its way back into the obesity-drug game after fighting off a rival bid from Novo Nordisk to buy Metsera. More money and help from the Trump administration.

news.title: I have $12K in credit-card debt due to health issues and a 30% pay cut. Is it finally time to take a loan from my 401(k)?
news.summary: “Because of a downturn in my industry, my pay was cut 30%.” “My pay was Cut 30%’ “I’ve had to take a pay cut of 30%. I’m not happy.”

news.title: By one measure the bull market is 16 years old. Here’s why investors face a ‘challenging decade’ ahead.
news.summary: Some of the long-term supportive tailwinds are shifting, according to MRB. Some of the support for the U.S. economy is shifting, MRB says.
